{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PYRcD3fYUcmXJzmWDw2UTa","type":"tool_result","content":"   195→function isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(text: string): boolean {\n   196→  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n   197→  return ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS.has(normalized);\n   198→}\n   199→\n   200→function isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n   201→  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n   202→  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n   203→}\n   204→\n   205→function looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n   206→  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n   207→}\n   208→\n   209→function isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n   210→  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n   211→  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n   212→\n   213→  // Pipe embedded in words = OCR artifact (e.g., \"Sp|aszcz\", \"pa|ką\")\n   214→  if (/[a-zA-ZÀ-ÿа-яА-Я]\\|[a-zA-ZÀ-ÿа-яА-Я]/.test(text)) return true;\n   215→\n   216→  // Mixed Latin + Cyrillic = OCR corruption\n   217→  if (/[а-яА-ЯёЁіІїЇєЄґҐ]/.test(text) && /[a-zA-Z]/.test(text)) return true;\n   218→\n   219→  // Check vowel ratio — English/Polish text typically has 30–50% vowels\n   220→  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYąęóĄĘÓ]/g, \"\").length;\n   221→  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n   222→  if (vowelRatio < 0.10 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n   223→\n   224→  // Single orphaned word ≤3 letters that isn't a common word\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8fa50ac3-bb2e-41a0-ae5a